but I, if I were to speak to you,

00:17:19.259 --> 00:17:20.779
if you were in my place,

00:17:20.779 --> 00:17:22.619
if the roles were reversed,

00:17:22.619 --> 00:17:25.220
I could heap up words against you.

00:17:25.220 --> 00:17:27.179
I could shake mine head at you,

00:17:27.179 --> 00:17:30.659
but I would strengthen you with my mouth,

00:17:30.659 --> 00:17:34.539
and the moving of my lips should assuage your grief.

00:17:34.539 --> 00:17:37.059
That's his intent.

00:17:37.059 --> 00:17:38.220
That's his purpose.

00:17:38.220 --> 00:17:40.259
That's what he says he would do.

00:17:40.259 --> 00:17:42.739
But when I note the testimony of Job,

00:17:42.739 --> 00:17:45.859
really, if you go back to Job chapter number four,

00:17:45.859 --> 00:17:48.379
you find that that's exactly what Job did.

00:17:49.220 --> 00:17:52.220
Notice, turn back to Job chapter number four, if you will.

00:17:52.220 --> 00:17:53.379
It's very interesting.

00:17:54.459 --> 00:17:56.419
In Job chapter number four,

00:17:56.419 --> 00:17:59.579
we read the first speech of Eliphaz.

00:17:59.579 --> 00:18:01.379
Now remember, this is the fellow

00:18:01.379 --> 00:18:04.339
that Job is responding to,

00:18:04.339 --> 00:18:06.779
and it's really the second speech of Eliphaz

00:18:06.779 --> 00:18:10.220
that he's speaking to in chapter number 16,

00:18:11.059 --> 00:18:13.099
and he's responding to that particular speech,

00:18:13.099 --> 00:18:15.539
but we find that Job chapter number four

00:18:15.539 --> 00:18:17.619
records for us the first speech

00:18:17.619 --> 00:18:19.979
of this man Eliphaz the Temanite.

00:18:19.979 --> 00:18:22.419
Notice it says this in verse number one,

00:18:22.419 --> 00:18:24.899
then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said,

00:18:24.899 --> 00:18:27.739
if we say to commune with thee, wilt thou be grieved?

00:18:27.739 --> 00:18:30.500
But who can withhold himself from speaking?

00:18:30.500 --> 00:18:34.699
Notice what he says about Job in verses three and four.

00:18:34.699 --> 00:18:37.099
Now understand, in chapter number 16,

00:18:37.099 --> 00:18:38.739
we're reading the words of Job.

00:18:38.739 --> 00:18:41.459
We're reading that Job says, this is what I would do.

00:18:41.459 --> 00:18:43.580
I would strengthen you with my mouth.

00:18:43.580 --> 00:18:46.820
I would use my words to assuage your grief.

00:18:46.820 --> 00:18:48.619
But here in chapter number four,

00:18:48.619 --> 00:18:53.260
this is what Eliphaz is saying that Job did.

00:18:53.260 --> 00:18:58.260
Verse three, behold, thou hast instructed many,

00:18:59.779 --> 00:19:04.779
and thou hast strengthened the weak hands.

00:19:04.979 --> 00:19:08.140
Well, that's a great testimony, is it not?

00:19:08.500 --> 00:19:12.739
That Job was known by Eliphaz to do two things

00:19:12.739 --> 00:19:14.299
according to verse number three.

00:19:14.299 --> 00:19:18.019
Number one, he instructed, he instructed many.

00:19:19.140 --> 00:19:20.899
We know that as we read the book of Job

00:19:20.899 --> 00:19:22.260
and you go through the entirety of the book,

00:19:22.260 --> 00:19:27.260
you understand that Job was a very profitable man,

00:19:28.219 --> 00:19:31.260
been blessed by God in a very distinct way.

00:19:31.260 --> 00:19:33.140
And Job, according to verse number three,

00:19:33.140 --> 00:19:35.820
he had great influence because the Bible says

00:19:35.940 --> 00:19:39.940
that Eliphaz says thou hast instructed many.

00:19:40.820 --> 00:19:43.299
We can use our mouth, our words, our lips

00:19:43.299 --> 00:19:46.339
to instruct individuals, but we also notice

00:19:46.339 --> 00:19:48.739
that in verse number three, it says this,

00:19:48.739 --> 00:19:53.739
and thou hast strengthened the weak hands.

00:19:54.700 --> 00:19:57.500
What is it that Job said he would do?

00:19:57.500 --> 00:19:58.859
I would strengthen you.

00:19:58.859 --> 00:20:00.219
Is that not what he said?

00:20:00.219 --> 00:20:02.580
In verse number five of Job 16,

00:20:02.580 --> 00:20:05.059
he says I would strengthen you with my mouth.

00:20:05.059 --> 00:20:08.479
Well, Eliphaz said in his first speech, as he begins, he says,

00:20:08.479 --> 00:20:10.979
Job, you have instructed many,

00:20:10.979 --> 00:20:15.319
but also you have strengthened the weak hands.

00:20:15.319 --> 00:20:19.079
Notice verse number four, thy words.

00:20:19.079 --> 00:20:21.539
So we understand that's how Job did it, right?

00:20:21.539 --> 00:20:25.279
Job instructed, he strengthened the weak hands with his words.

00:20:25.279 --> 00:20:29.119
Thy words have upholden him that was falling,

00:20:29.119 --> 00:20:34.259
and thou hast strengthened the feeble knees.

00:20:34.499 --> 00:20:36.739
Well, praise the Lord for that testimony.

00:20:38.039 --> 00:20:41.279
That Job had this testimony that Eliphaz says,

00:20:41.279 --> 00:20:43.179
this is what you have done.

00:20:43.179 --> 00:20:47.499
Job, you have been in a position earlier in your life,

00:20:47.499 --> 00:20:49.439
many, many times in your life,

00:20:49.439 --> 00:20:50.739
you've been in the position

00:20:50.739 --> 00:20:52.619
where you've been able to instruct people.

00:20:52.619 --> 00:20:53.659
You've been in the position

00:20:53.659 --> 00:20:56.419
that you've been able to strengthen people.

00:20:56.419 --> 00:20:58.179
You have done this.

00:20:58.179 --> 00:21:00.419
Obviously, we find in verse number five, he says,

00:21:00.419 --> 00:21:02.299
but now it has come upon thee, and thou faintest,

00:21:02.299 --> 00:21:04.139
it touches thee, and thou art troubled.

00:21:04.979 --> 00:21:06.979
And so he's thinking that he's going to now share some words

00:21:06.979 --> 00:21:09.979
and try to help Job through this situation.

00:21:09.979 --> 00:21:12.979
And we find, even as we mentioned in our text in Job 16,

00:21:12.979 --> 00:21:14.459
that they're miserable comforters,

00:21:14.459 --> 00:21:17.059
and they did not use their words to strengthen

00:21:17.059 --> 00:21:20.759
or to instruct, but rather to these vain words

00:21:20.759 --> 00:21:24.899
that were used according to what we read in Job chapter 19,

00:21:24.899 --> 00:21:26.699
that they were vexing his soul

00:21:26.699 --> 00:21:31.619
and breaking in pieces his bones with their words.

00:21:31.619 --> 00:21:35.379
And so this evening, as we look at this simple thought

00:21:35.379 --> 00:21:38.899
in this few passages of scripture from the book of Job,

00:21:38.899 --> 00:21:42.899
I find that there's a lesson for us

00:21:42.899 --> 00:21:47.059
with regard to our words and how we would use our words.

00:21:47.059 --> 00:21:50.579
We understand that God says much about our speech,

00:21:50.579 --> 00:21:53.500
and our speech, we've mentioned a few other verses

00:21:53.500 --> 00:21:54.979
throughout the scriptures this evening,

00:21:54.979 --> 00:21:58.379
and the word of God obviously gives us instruction

00:21:58.379 --> 00:22:01.180
as to how we are to speak and the things that we are to say,

00:22:01.180 --> 00:22:02.739
but I would ask this evening,

00:22:04.699 --> 00:22:07.459
are we more like the friends of Job,

00:22:07.459 --> 00:22:08.779
or are we more like Job?

00:22:11.220 --> 00:22:15.580
Are we using our words to strengthen,

00:22:16.500 --> 00:22:21.500
to comfort, to help assuage the grief of those

00:22:21.739 --> 00:22:23.860
that we come into contact with,

00:22:23.860 --> 00:22:27.860
or are we coming in with these words that are vain words?

00:22:27.860 --> 00:22:31.779
Are we hurting people instead of helping people?

00:22:32.819 --> 00:22:35.699
See, there's a great contrast in Job 16.

00:22:36.660 --> 00:22:39.860
And the reality is that these friends,

00:22:39.860 --> 00:22:41.619
according to Job 2 and verse number 11,

00:22:41.619 --> 00:22:42.860
I have not read that verse too,

00:22:42.860 --> 00:22:43.979
I've referenced it a few times,

00:22:43.979 --> 00:22:45.179
but if you want to look at it,

00:22:45.179 --> 00:22:46.539
just so you can see what it says,

00:22:46.539 --> 00:22:48.819
now, when Job's three friends heard of all this evil

00:22:48.819 --> 00:22:50.099
that was come upon him,

00:22:50.099 --> 00:22:51.779
they came, everyone from his own place,

00:22:51.779 --> 00:22:54.459
Eliphaz the Tammanite, and Bildad the Shuhite,

00:22:54.459 --> 00:22:56.020
and Zophar the Namathite,

00:22:56.020 --> 00:22:58.660
for they had made an appointment together,

00:22:58.660 --> 00:23:02.580
notice, to come to mourn with him and to comfort him.

00:23:05.339 --> 00:23:07.220
But they were miserable comforters.

00:23:07.220 --> 00:23:08.300
They didn't use their words.

00:23:08.300 --> 00:23:11.979
They were not successful at using their words

00:23:11.979 --> 00:23:15.139
for the stated purpose of Job 2 and verse number 11.

00:23:15.139 --> 00:23:16.979
So if we were to evaluate our words,

00:23:16.979 --> 00:23:18.500
our speech this evening,

00:23:18.500 --> 00:23:22.419
would we align more with Job,

00:23:22.459 --> 00:23:24.819
as it says in chapter 4,

00:23:24.819 --> 00:23:29.059
instructing many, strengthening the weak hands,

00:23:29.059 --> 00:23:32.699
thy words have upholden him that was falling,

00:23:32.699 --> 00:23:36.779
thou hast strengthened the feeble knees,

00:23:36.779 --> 00:23:40.459
or would we align more with the friends of Job?

00:23:40.459 --> 00:23:43.779
Eliphaz specifically being spoken to in chapter 16,

00:23:43.779 --> 00:23:48.139
Bildad specifically being spoken to in chapter 19,

00:23:48.139 --> 00:23:53.139
vain words, hurtful words, destructive words,

00:23:53.300 --> 00:23:57.779
death and life are in the power of the tongue.

00:23:57.779 --> 00:23:59.580
And this evening, when we think about our words

00:23:59.580 --> 00:24:01.259
and we just evaluate,

00:24:01.259 --> 00:24:03.580
and we think about this simple thought

00:24:03.580 --> 00:24:04.979
from the book of Job,

00:24:04.979 --> 00:24:06.779
I believe that when we keep this in mind

00:24:06.779 --> 00:24:08.779
and when we pray the prayer that the psalmist prayed

00:24:08.779 --> 00:24:11.419
in Psalm 19 and verse number 14,

00:24:11.419 --> 00:24:12.739
it would cause us to be in a position

00:24:12.739 --> 00:24:15.300
where we have to think before we speak.

00:24:15.300 --> 00:24:18.699
We have to be calculated in the things that we say.

00:24:18.699 --> 00:24:21.220
Speak the truth in love.

00:24:22.179 --> 00:24:23.579
Speak the truth in love.

00:24:23.579 --> 00:24:25.019
You know, it's interesting to me,

00:24:25.019 --> 00:24:27.100
if you study the Bible,

00:24:27.100 --> 00:24:28.980
of course, obviously you're going to learn

00:24:28.980 --> 00:24:31.299
a lot of wonderful things if you study the Bible,

00:24:31.299 --> 00:24:34.019
and what a simple statement.

00:24:34.899 --> 00:24:36.660
But I think about the Apostle Paul.

00:24:38.500 --> 00:24:41.380
Paul said some things to some people,

00:24:41.380 --> 00:24:43.380
to some of the churches and some of the individuals

00:24:43.419 --> 00:24:46.820
that he ministered to that were

00:24:49.380 --> 00:24:53.299
direct and could have been hurtful things,

00:24:54.700 --> 00:24:56.459
but he said them in love.

00:24:57.859 --> 00:25:00.779
If you look at the book of First Thessalonians,

00:25:00.779 --> 00:25:02.739
when he speaks to the believers of Thessalonica,

00:25:02.739 --> 00:25:05.540
he tells those believers that he desired

00:25:05.540 --> 00:25:07.660
to send Timothy unto them

00:25:07.660 --> 00:25:09.739
so that Timothy could perfect that

00:25:09.739 --> 00:25:13.220
which was lacking in their faith.

00:25:14.059 --> 00:25:14.899
Now, when you're telling somebody

00:25:14.899 --> 00:25:16.299
that they have some areas in which they need to grow

00:25:16.299 --> 00:25:18.700
that you're lacking in your faith,

00:25:18.700 --> 00:25:20.380
that could be taken wrong.

00:25:22.459 --> 00:25:24.179
But you know, it doesn't seem that the believers

00:25:24.179 --> 00:25:26.100
in Thessalonica took it wrong

00:25:26.100 --> 00:25:29.540
because they knew that Paul was speaking it in love.

00:25:29.540 --> 00:25:31.459
He was trying to help them.

00:25:31.459 --> 00:25:35.100
He said, listen, there's some instruction that's needed

00:25:35.100 --> 00:25:37.100
and we're going to provide a means

00:25:37.100 --> 00:25:40.179
in which that instruction can be provided.

00:25:40.220 --> 00:25:43.220
And so the reality is that we,

00:25:43.220 --> 00:25:45.059
it's not that we would use our words

00:25:45.059 --> 00:25:47.299
that we would just lie to people to make them feel good.

00:25:47.299 --> 00:25:50.019
That's not the point of what I'm saying this evening.

00:25:50.019 --> 00:25:52.179
We need to speak the truth.

00:25:53.100 --> 00:25:57.339
We speak it in love and we speak calculated.

00:25:57.339 --> 00:26:02.339
How can my words strengthen this individual?

00:26:02.899 --> 00:26:06.820
How can my words help assuage the grief

00:26:06.820 --> 00:26:08.940
that this individual is enduring

00:26:09.019 --> 00:26:10.940
at this particular time in their life?

00:26:12.019 --> 00:26:16.019
We begin to see that as we would evaluate our own words

00:26:16.019 --> 00:26:18.260
and our own opportunities,

00:26:18.260 --> 00:26:21.380
perhaps we could look at these comparisons,

00:26:21.380 --> 00:26:23.339
this contrast, if you will,

00:26:23.339 --> 00:26:26.619
between the words of Job and the words of his friends.

00:26:26.619 --> 00:26:30.100
And I just ask for a simple, I guess,

00:26:30.100 --> 00:26:32.579
evaluation of ourselves.

00:26:32.579 --> 00:26:34.619
On what side would we align?

00:26:34.619 --> 00:26:38.500
Would we align more with Job or more with his friends?

00:26:39.019 --> 00:26:41.380
I hope this evening that the answer would be

00:26:41.380 --> 00:26:43.660
that we align with Job.

00:26:44.619 --> 00:26:48.380
That we are using our words to strengthen,

00:26:48.380 --> 00:26:50.059
to help assuage the grief,

00:26:50.059 --> 00:26:53.459
to help strengthen those that are weak.

00:26:54.380 --> 00:26:57.220
And God will allow us to do so.

00:26:58.260 --> 00:26:59.459
We need to think.

00:26:59.459 --> 00:27:02.500
We need to be calculated in how we speak.

00:27:02.500 --> 00:27:07.260
Job says that he would strengthen them

00:27:07.260 --> 00:27:08.419
with the words of his mouth,

00:27:08.419 --> 00:27:10.579
or with his mouth he would strengthen them.

00:27:10.579 --> 00:27:12.019
And what a blessing.

00:27:12.019 --> 00:27:14.540
And not only do we see he intended to do that,

00:27:14.540 --> 00:27:16.100
he said that's what he would do,

00:27:16.100 --> 00:27:19.459
but he was known to have done that.

00:27:19.459 --> 00:27:21.260
That was his practice,

00:27:21.260 --> 00:27:24.940
according to what Eliphaz says of him in Job 4.

00:27:24.940 --> 00:27:27.380
What a great testimony that Job had.

00:27:27.380 --> 00:27:30.339
And oh, that we too would have a similar testimony.

00:27:30.339 --> 00:27:31.179
Let's pray.

00:27:31.179 --> 00:27:32.419
Father, we love you.

00:27:32.419 --> 00:27:34.700
We thank you for loving us.

00:27:34.700 --> 00:27:38.100
God, I pray that you would help us

00:27:38.100 --> 00:27:39.619
to evaluate our speech,

00:27:39.619 --> 00:27:43.299
that we would pray as the psalmist prayed in Psalm 19,

00:27:43.299 --> 00:27:45.820
let the words of my mouth and the meditation of my heart

00:27:45.820 --> 00:27:48.500
be acceptable in thy sight.

00:27:48.500 --> 00:27:52.019
That we would understand that we're to use our words

00:27:52.019 --> 00:27:54.419
according to what Paul tells the believers in Ephesus

00:27:54.419 --> 00:27:58.220
for the edifying of the brethren.

00:27:58.220 --> 00:28:01.380
Father, I pray that you'd help us to align with Job,

00:28:01.380 --> 00:28:03.500
that we would be purposed and calculated

00:28:03.540 --> 00:28:05.059
in the things that we would say,

00:28:05.059 --> 00:28:06.779
that we might be used of thee

00:28:06.779 --> 00:28:09.980
to help strengthen those that are weak,

00:28:09.980 --> 00:28:12.779
that we might help to assuage the grief

00:28:12.779 --> 00:28:15.820
of those that are enduring hardship.

00:28:15.820 --> 00:28:19.859
Lord, help us to speak the truth in love.

00:28:21.139 --> 00:28:22.980
I pray that you'd bless our time of prayer.

00:28:22.980 --> 00:28:24.739
We thank you so much for the privilege

00:28:24.739 --> 00:28:27.339
